# ⚔️ Ironhold Chess

> **Two Armies · One Board · No Mercy**

**Ironhold Chess** is an original browser-based chess experience that turns traditional chess captures into animated battlefield encounters.

Instead of using conventional chess piece images, every piece is represented by a custom-built SVG warrior silhouette. When a capture occurs, the attacking piece charges into battle, the defending piece reacts and falls, impact effects appear, smoke rises from the battlefield, and the board shakes from the collision.

This is chess — presented as warfare.

---

## 🎮 Play

**[Play Ironhold Chess](https://adithyanhp.github.io/Ironhold-Chess/)**

No installation is required.

Open the game in a modern browser and start playing.

---

## ⚔️ What Makes Ironhold Chess Different?

Most chess games treat a capture as a simple piece disappearing from the board.

Ironhold Chess treats a capture as a battle.

```text
Normal Chess:

♙ × ♟
Piece captured.

Ironhold Chess:

⚔️
The attacker charges.
The defender reacts.
Impact strikes.
Smoke rises.
The battlefield shakes.
The piece falls.
```

The game combines a traditional chess engine with a custom visual combat system built entirely in the browser.

---

## ✨ Features

### ♟️ Complete Chess Rules

The game includes core chess rules and legality validation:

* Standard piece movement
* Legal move generation
* Check detection
* Checkmate detection
* Stalemate detection
* Castling
* En passant
* Pawn promotion
* Move notation
* Turn management

Moves are validated before they are executed, including protection against moves that leave the player's own king in check.

---

### 🤖 Play Against the Ironhold AI

Play against the built-in chess AI or challenge another player locally.

#### Game Modes

* **Two Players**
* **Vs. The Ironhold AI**

#### AI Strength

* **Recruit** — Easy
* **Veteran** — Medium
* **Warlord** — Hard

The AI uses a minimax search algorithm with alpha-beta pruning.

Its evaluation considers:

* Piece material value
* Board positioning
* Central control
* Checkmate positions
* Search depth

```text
AI Search

Current Position
       │
       ▼
Generate Legal Moves
       │
       ▼
Simulate Positions
       │
       ▼
Evaluate Positions
       │
       ▼
Minimax Search
       │
       ▼
Alpha-Beta Pruning
       │
       ▼
Select Best Move
```

---

### ⚔️ Animated Battle Captures

Captures are the central visual feature of Ironhold Chess.

When a piece captures another piece, the game creates a temporary battle scene directly on the board.

The battle sequence can include:

* Attacker movement
* Weapon animations
* Defender impact reaction
* Defender collapse
* Impact flash
* Smoke particles
* Board shake
* Procedural combat sounds

The battle animation is generated dynamically based on the attacking and defending pieces.

---

### 🛡️ Custom SVG Warrior Pieces

Every chess piece is drawn programmatically using SVG.

The piece designs are not standard chess icons.

They are custom battlefield silhouettes with articulated components such as:

* Heads
* Torsos
* Arms
* Legs
* Weapons
* Crowns
* Shields
* Mounts
* Magical elements

Different pieces have different visual identities and animation behavior.

For example:

| Piece  | Battlefield Identity |
| ------ | -------------------- |
| Pawn   | Infantry warrior     |
| Knight | Mounted warrior      |
| Bishop | Mystical warrior     |
| Rook   | Heavy warrior        |
| Queen  | Elite warrior        |
| King   | Crowned warlord      |

---

### 🎭 Piece-Specific Combat Animation

The combat system uses different animation styles for different warrior types.

Animations include:

* Sword swings
* Weapon thrusts
* Spinning attacks
* Mounted knight attacks
* Body movement
* Head movement
* Leg movement
* Torso rotation
* Magical orb effects

The attacker does not simply move from one square to another.

It performs an animated attack.

---

### 💥 Impact Effects

Captures trigger multiple visual effects:

* Impact flash
* Screen shake on the board
* Smoke wisps
* Defender knockback
* Defender collapse
* Animated attacker movement

The battle overlay is created dynamically and removed after the combat animation finishes.

---

### 🔊 Procedural Sound Effects

Ironhold Chess uses the browser's **Web Audio API** to generate sound effects.

Current sound effects include:

* Piece movement
* Captures
* Check notifications
* Impact noise
* Procedural white noise effects

Sound can be toggled on or off at any time.

---

### 🎨 Four Visual Army Palettes

The battlefield can be visually transformed using four color palettes:

#### 🔥 Molten Gold

Gold vs Deep Obsidian

#### 🌈 Neon

Neon Cyan vs Neon Pink

#### ❄️ Ice

Ice Blue vs Fire Red

#### 💀 Blood Moon

Bone White vs Blood Red

Each palette changes the visual identity of the two opposing armies.

---

### 📜 Battle Chronicle

Every move is recorded in the Chronicle panel.

The move history displays:

* Move numbers
* White moves
* Black moves
* Check notation
* Checkmate notation

The chronicle automatically scrolls as the battle progresses.

---

### ☠️ Captured Pieces

Captured pieces are tracked separately for both armies.

The game displays:

* Pieces captured by White
* Pieces captured by Black
* Captured piece icons
* Current material advantage

The material difference is calculated using standard piece values:

```text
Pawn   = 100
Knight = 320
Bishop = 330
Rook   = 500
Queen  = 900
King   = 0
```

---

### ↩️ Undo Moves

The game includes an undo system.

In AI mode, undoing a move goes back through the player's previous turn and the AI's response, allowing the player to reconsider the position.

---

### 🔄 Flip the Board

Rotate the board to view the battlefield from the opposite side.

Useful for:

* Two-player games
* Different board orientations
* Viewing the game from the opponent's perspective

---

### 🏆 Game End States

The game detects:

* Checkmate
* Stalemate
* Draws

When the battle ends, the game displays a dedicated result state.

Examples include:

```text
White wins by checkmate
Black wins by checkmate
Draw by stalemate
```

The game also displays battlefield-style result messages such as:

```text
⚔ VICTORY BY CHECKMATE ⚔

⚔ THE BATTLE ENDS IN A DRAW ⚔
```

---

## 🕹️ How to Play

### 1. Select a Game Mode

Choose between:

* Two Players
* Vs. The Ironhold AI

---

### 2. Choose AI Strength

If playing against the AI, select:

* Recruit
* Veteran
* Warlord

---

### 3. Select an Army Palette

Choose from four visual themes:

* Gold
* Neon
* Ice
* Blood

---

### 4. Select a Piece

Click one of your pieces.

Legal destinations will be displayed on the board.

---

### 5. Make Your Move

Click a highlighted legal square.

If the move is a capture, the battle animation begins.

---

## 🎮 Controls

| Action              | Control              |
| ------------------- | -------------------- |
| Select a piece      | Click                |
| Move a piece        | Click a legal square |
| Promote a pawn      | Select a champion    |
| Start a new game    | New Campaign         |
| Undo a move         | Undo Move            |
| Rotate the board    | Flip Board           |
| Toggle sound        | Sound: On / Off      |
| Change visual theme | Army Colors          |

---

## 🛠️ Technology

Ironhold Chess is built using web technologies without a framework or build system.

### Core Technologies

* HTML5
* CSS3
* JavaScript
* SVG
* CSS Animations
* Web Audio API

### AI

* Minimax
* Alpha-beta pruning
* Material evaluation
* Positional evaluation
* Legal move generation

### Rendering

* Dynamic DOM rendering
* Programmatically generated SVG warriors
* CSS animation system
* Temporary battle overlays
* Particle-style smoke effects

---

## 🧱 Architecture

Ironhold Chess is implemented as a self-contained browser application.

```text
┌──────────────────────────────┐
│          User Interface       │
│                              │
│  Board · Controls · Chronicle │
│  Captured Pieces · Status     │
└──────────────┬───────────────┘
               │
               ▼
┌──────────────────────────────┐
│         Chess Engine          │
│                              │
│  Move Generation              │
│  Legality Validation          │
│  Check Detection              │
│  Checkmate Detection          │
│  Stalemate Detection          │
│  Castling                     │
│  En Passant                   │
│  Promotion                    │
└──────────────┬───────────────┘
               │
               ▼
┌──────────────────────────────┐
│             AI               │
│                              │
│  Position Evaluation          │
│  Minimax                      │
│  Alpha-Beta Pruning           │
└──────────────┬───────────────┘
               │
               ▼
┌──────────────────────────────┐
│       Battle Presentation     │
│                              │
│  SVG Warriors                 │
│  Attack Animations            │
│  Impact Effects               │
│  Smoke Effects                │
│  Board Shake                  │
│  Sound Effects                │
└──────────────────────────────┘
```

